These are made in an §3EBF§r with §2Kanthal§r or better coils, and need §2Nitrogen§r for the process. It needs twice as much Silicon as the basic boules, but also results in twice as many doped Silicon Wafers when sliced.

Circuit Wafers can be made far more efficiently with these doped Silicon Wafers, but they are also needed for some more advanced types of Circuit Wafers that can't be engraved onto the basic ones.

FUSION!

This baby can do any fusion recipe, notably giving you access to §6Neutronium§r.

The multiblock layout is the same as the Mark 1 and Mark 2, with the same hatch and casing substitutions permitted.

Obviously though, this one uses §6Fusion Machine Casing Mk §2III§r and only works with §aUV Energy Hatches§r.

The §3Mark 3 Fusion Reactor§r has an energy buffer of §e640M EU§r.

§2Doesn't look exactly like Europium anymore.§r

To make §9Tritanium§r, you first need to make §9Duranium§r. This is done by fusing molten §9Gallium§r and §9Radon§r in a §3Fusion Reactor Mark 1§r or better.

Once you have Duranium, you can fuse Tritanium in a §3Fusion Reactor Mark 2§r using the Duranium and molten §9Titanium§r.

If you're having trouble figuring out the right item and fluid ratios for batching up these processes, consider plugging the relevant recipes into the §aCrafting Calculator§r.

§6RTM Alloy§r is an alloy of §6Ruthenium, Tungsten§r and §6Molybdenum§r.

This alloy is cooked in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r and cooled in a §3Vacuum Freezer§r.

With §6Tungstensteel§r achieved, you can now make hulls for Insane Voltage (IV) §bGregTech§r machines.

This unlocks shortcut recipes for §bAE2 §6Processors§r in the §3Circuit Assembler§r.

§2Starting at IV, 16A Energy and Dynamo hatches are available at each tier.§r

§6Yttrium Barium Cuprate§r (more accurately, Yttrium Barium Copper Oxide, or YBCO) is, among other things, a high-temperature superconductor material.

This is used as plates in §bNuclearCraft§r, and will become an important cable material for later tiers of §bGregTech§r components.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§6Tungsten§r is a material that requires an §3EV Electrolyzer§r, §2Chemical Bath§r and an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r with at least §6Nichrome Coils§r.

It is only found from §6Tungstate §2Dust and Scheelite Dust, obtained from their respective ores.§r Tungstate is also obtainable in small quantities from centrifuging §6Endstone Dust§r.

Scheelite and Tungstate needs to be §2bathed in Hydrochloric Acid to make Tungstic Acid, then electrolyzed§r to get to the Tungsten, which then needs to be cooked in the EBF for Tungsten ingots.

This is one of the simpler rockets you can build. The specifics of the shape don't really matter as long as the rocket engines are on the bottom and all the parts are added. It also needs to be inside the edges of the Launch Pad and not taller than the Structure Tower.

§aIn order to progress this quest chain further, you'll first need to complete the Interdimensional Transport (either FTB Warps/Homes, Dislocators or Telepad) questline and the Rocket Fuel questline, both of which are nearby on this quest tab.§r
Marginally cheaper to make than §2Advanced Integrated Circuits§r, and also the only way to make the §2Workstation§r, which is the first Tier Four circuit.

Making yourself a space suit is the most important step towards your space adventures.

This suit lets you breathe in space, which is kind of important.

If you can afford the recipe, you can also apply the §dAirtight Seal§r enchant to all four pieces of your armor to make it act like a space suit. §cIt still needs to be refilled at a Gas Pad occasionally!§r

The Suit Workstation is needed to install §6Low Pressure Tanks§r (or a larger tank if you like) onto your Space Suit Chest-Piece.

Once installed, you can stand on a §3Gas Charging Pad§r to fill up the tanks with §9Oxygen§r. Of course, you'll need to fill the Gas Charging Pad with Oxygen first, using something like a fluid conduit.

If you choose to use §dAirtight Seal§r enchants instead of a space suit, you'll only need a Gas Charging Pad.
A common component used by §bExtended Crafting§r.
Combine several components into a catalyst.

At some point you might consider venturing into space, like the Moon. While it's not at all required for the progression, you might find it valuable: to say the least, the Moon contains ore veins which are not found in the Overworld. And for this, you'll need a rocket and a whole lot of preparations.

Before you can build the rocket itself, you'll need to create a launch pad. The §6Launch Pad§r blocks go in a 3x3 layout flat on the ground to form the platform.

The Structure Tower is formed from a column of §6Structure Tower§r blocks that holds your rocket upright. The first block goes adjacent to any side of the launch pad platform (on the same Y-level as the launch pad blocks).

With 6 Structure Tower blocks, you can only build a rocket 5 blocks high, since any higher would exceed the height of the tower. To build a taller rocket, you'll need to build a taller tower using more Structure Tower blocks.

The §3Rocket Assembling Machine§r needs to be placed next to the launch pad (not on it) 1 block higher than the platform, so that the bottom of the Rocket Assembler is flush with the top of the launch pad. It also needs to be supplied with RF power to function.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Launch Pad and Rocket Assembly Machine

betterquesting:10.desc:8: With the Extended Crafting Table, you can now craft 5x5 recipes.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

You'll need this to set the §aGuidance Computer's§r destination to the Moon (Luna).

In your assembled Rocket, press the Rocket GUI Hotkey (default is §eCtrl/Cmd + C§r). Click the little square that says "Guidance Computer" to pull up the Guidance Computer inventory. Then, place the blank chip into the Guidance Computer. Back out of this menu (§eEsc§r or §eE§r) to get back to the main Rocket GUI.

Click the §cSelect Dst§r button, choose Luna, and click the Select button to assign the destination to the chip.

§eNote: if you want to return your rocket to Earth, you will need to change the destination in this manner again to Earth before launching.§r

The §3Fueling Station§r is how rockets get fuel.

First, put together your Rocket, then §aScan§r and §cBuild§r the Rocket in the §3Rocket Assembling Machine§r to assemble it (which turns it into an entity). Next, with the §aLinker§r in your hand, right-click the Fueling Station then the Rocket Assembling Machine to link the Fueling Station to the constructed Rocket.

You'll get a confirmation message when you do it right, and a little line will appear between the Fueling Station and the rocket.

Now just get §9Rocket Fuel§r into the Fueling Station and it will transfer to the Rocket automatically.

Holding one of these reveals §aTravel Anchors§r and §aTelepads§r in range.

Shift + right-click after aiming to warp to one, or point it anywhere to teleport forward a short distance (works through walls).

These are powered with RF, and can be further enchanted through §bEnderIO§r's enchanting mechanics.

Alternatively, you can search the §eLost Cities§r or make a Travel §6Dark Steel§r Upgrade, and apply it to your
§bEnderIO§r tools.

The §6Vibrant Crystal§r will require an §3Autoclave§r.

If you went to the §eMoon§r you have the option of using §6Moon Dust§r or a §3Fluid Rig§r to produce the Deuterium you need to get the §6Microversium§r for your first §3Microverse Projector§r.

Your other options are to centrifuge or distill §9Ender Air§r, or to centrifuge §9Hydrogen§r. How you choose to proceed is up to you.

Once you have §9Deuterium§r, smelt some §6Microversium§r. Soon you'll be launching your §6Micro Miners§r into another universe!

§2Pumps are now available in GT.§r

Useful for gathering §6Oil§r, or perhaps §6Lava§r from the §cNether§r.

This is your first §3Microverse Projector§r.

These structures are used to project §6Micro Miners§r into a §eMicroverse§r to obtain valuable loot such as §6ores§r, §6gems§r, and otherwise unobtainable items like §6Radium Salt§r and §6Naquadah Dust§r. §cKeep in mind that Micro Miners are single-use!§r

Microverse Projectors are §bGregTech§r multiblocks, which means that they're just as flexible as other machines in terms of the I/O block placement: §epositions of Buses and Hatches can be swapped with any Microverse Projector Casing§r.

A single §6HV Energy Input§r supports missions up to 1024 EU/t. To process the rest, you'll need to upgrade the multiblock to at least §eEV power§r, which is either §6two HV Energy Inputs§r or §6one EV Energy Input§r. Missions will also overclock, increasing in speed each time the projector's energy tier increases and available power reaches the next multiple of four times the base mission power.

Hover your mouse over the Small Microverse Projector and press §bU§r to see all available missions.

§6Sneak-right click§r the controller to enable the in-world preview.

This is your first §bMicro Miner. §2You'll need that Phosphorous in the LV Field Generators.§r
Yes, not the last: these things aren't reusable.

This one can get you:
§6* Dense Iron Ore
* Cassiterite Ore
* Redstone Ore
* Nickel Ore
§2* Ilmenite Ore
§6* Uraninite Ore
* Galena Ore
§2* Molybdenum Ore
§6* Moon Turf
* Dilithium
* Salt Ore§r

When equipped with a §bGemstone Sensor§r (which may currently not be available to you yet):
§2* Perfect Diamond
§6* Apatite Ore
* Tricalcium Phosphate Ore
* Quartzite Ore§r

Can also be used to bring §bStellar Creation Data§r, but less efficiently than the Tier Two.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.
Scatter a few around your base, and you can warp to anywhere you please!

Mix §9Oxygen§r and §91,1-Dimethylhydrazine§r together to make §9Rocket Fuel§r.

Awesome!

When you have stable sourcing for Nitrogen and Oxygen, you can make and use §9Dinitrogen Tetroxide§r in the recipe instead of Oxygen. It doubles the efficiency of your 1,1-Dimethylhydrazine when making Rocket Fuel.
§9Dimethylamine§r and §9Chloramine§r combine together into §91,1-Dimethylhydrazine§r. §2Or, combine Methanol, Ammonia and Hypochlorous Acid in a LCR.§r

§9Methanol§r and §9Ammonia§r combine together to make §9Dimethylamine§r.

I know you're expecting a Breaking Bad joke here, but I don't walt to go for such low hanging fruit.

§2This step can be skipped with a Large Chemical Reactor.§r
§9Hypochlorous Acid§r and §9Ammonia§r combine together to make §9Chloramine§r. §2This step can be skipped with LCRs.§r

§9Hydrogen§r and §9Nitrogen§r combine together to make §9Ammonia§r.

An easy way to get Nitrogen is to centrifuge §9Air§r, which will require you to build an §3Air Collector§r. You could also electrolyze §6Saltpeter§r, distill §9Fermented Biomass§r in a §3Distillation Tower§r, or get huge amounts from §2distilling Liquid Air in a Distillation Tower.§r

§9Oxygen§r, §9Hydrogen§r, and §6Carbon§r combine together in a §3Chemical Reactor§r to make §9Methanol§r.

You can also use a §3Distillation Tower§r to get Methanol from §9Wood Vinegar§r and §9Fermented Biomass§r.

§9Water§r and §9Chlorine§r can be combined to make §9Hypochlorous Acid§r. If you add §9Mercury§r to catalyze the reaction, the yield is much better.

§ePlease note that Hypochlorous Acid and Hydrochloric Acid are different things.§r

You're already familiar with Chlorine production from your forays into Plastics, but a great source of Mercury is §2centrifuging §6Redstone§r.

Here comes the chemistry.

It might seem crazy right now, but you'll want a dedicated §3Chemical Reactor§r for pretty much every chemical you want to process. You probably want to hold off on doing that until you've got a solid base of autocrafting though... it stings a lot less when you can just request crafts of Chemical Reactors from your AE2 system.

Yes, Snad.

This pack has §aSnad§r, which is simply a sand-like block that instantly grows sugar cane/cactus on top of it when it receives either a block update or a redstone update.

The sugar cane it produces can be used as a fuel for your dynamos, and later you can even brew it for §9Biomass§r.

The premier way to activate Snad is with a §6Redstone Conduit§r. By force-connecting the conduit to the side of the Snad block with a Wrench, and inserting a §aSensor Filter§r, you can get the highest growth rate possible. Simpler methods such as a §aRedstone Clock§r can also work, but not as effectively.

To collect the sugar cane, you can use a piston and an observer. Later you can make an §6Auto-Breaker§r from §bActually Additions§r, which works even better and doesn't spill sugar cane everywhere.

For now, a §3Vacuum Chest§r should help keep the floor clean, and causes less lag than Hoppers. A §aVoid Upgrade§r in a §6Storage Drawer§r will automatically delete any items that overflow the drawer's capacity, so it's a good way to ensure you don't crash your server from accumulating a massive sugar cane pile before safer block breakers are available to you.

There's a great deal of interesting content within §bExtra Utilities 2§r, and although most of it is not required for progression, you should still look through what it offers and build what interests you.

In particular, the §aAngel Ring§r bauble offers creative flight, and although some of the RF generators are not particularly good, others are quite competitive with the Dynamos. And of course, you can aim for the all powerful §aRainbow Generator§r as you work towards endgame. All that and much more await, so explore away!

If you've tried to insert or remove a lot of items quickly, you might notice your ME network
§eflickers offline§r briefly. This is because digitizing and re-materializing items requires energy!

Your network doesn't naturally store very much energy and the §6Energy Acceptor§r only intermittently refills the network's power. To keep things stable, you will need to add some energy storage in your network using §6Energy Cells§r.

Just place one anywhere in your network and it will fill up with AE energy received from the Energy Acceptor. Now, you should have enough energy in your network to prevent these power losses. Feel free to add more energy cells, or upgrade to §6Dense Energy Cells§r, if you continue to experience problems.

If you've opted to enable channels in your AE2 configs, you will innately have some energy storage from the §3ME Controller§r, but we assume you know what you're doing at that point. §eAE2 Channels mechanics are outside the scope of the quest book, and this is the only time it will be mentioned.§r

Endervoirs are blocks that generate water much faster than basic NuclearCraft infinite water sources.

Endervoirs are multiblocks formed by at least three Endervoir blocks. You can right-click a block with a wrench to make it output into adjacent machines.

The maximum transfer rate of an Endervoir is one bucket per second.

With your Rocket built, fuel loaded, and destination set, it's time for the prelaunch checklist.

- §eMake sure you're wearing your Space Suit§r (all four pieces) and that it has a full tank of Oxygen. If you plan to stay on the Moon a while, maybe bring a gas charging pad and Ender Tank (being filled with Oxygen) with you.

When it comes to teleportation to and from the Moon you have some options:

- If using §bFTB Homes§r, use /sethome moon to set a home on the moon, which you can return to with /home moon.

- If you decided to go with §aDislocators§r, make sure you take two with you: one bound to the Overworld, the other ready to bind to the Moon. Also bring along a Pedestal to put the Overworld one on the Moon surface.

- If you decided to go with §aTelepads§r, make sure you've constructed a Telepad in the Overworld and that you're carrying coordinates that lead to it. Make sure to bring your Coordinate Selector, blank Paper, and materials for the second Telepad setup. Bring Dew of the Void and RF power (like a §6Solar Panel§r and a §6Capacitor Bank§r). §cRemember to chunkload the Telepad on the Moon!§r

When you're sure you're prepared, sit in your rocket and press §eSpace§r.

Liftoff!

There's a great deal of interesting content within §bActually Additions§r, and although most of it is not strictly required for progression, you should still look through what it offers and build what interests you.

§2The Drill is overpowered by the GregTech Drill, however it is still an option, as AA Drills do not have or lose durability. The Vertical Digger has been completely removed, as it is replaced by the GregTech single-block miners, and multi-block Ore Drilling Plants.

§3Phantomfaces§r, §3Auto Placers/Breakers§r, §3Lava Factories§r, and much more can be utilized at your discretion to supplement and refine your automation techniques.

§6Barium§r is an element found in §6Barite§r, which may be found as §6Barite Ore§r, inside §6Quartz§r veins.

Barite can also be extracted from other Quartz ores via ore processing, §2and Naquadah Processing, available in LuV.§r
Melting §6Mana Dust§r in a §2Extractor§r produces §9Primal Mana§r, which is needed for smelting various alloys from §bThermal Expansion§r.

§6Transistors§r are semiconductors that can amplify or switch electrical signals and power. They're probably one of the most important inventions of the 20th century.

You're going to use them as a component for better circuits. This one is a bit pricey, requiring §2PE, Silicon Plates and Fine Tin Wire.§r

§bApplied Energistics§r uses §aPresses§r found in chests at the heart of meteors as templates for §3Inscribers§r to make §6inscribed circuits§r.

This compass will lead you to the nearest meteor impact. Use your favorite mining tools to smash through the §6Skystone§r shell and get to the juicy center where the §6Skystone Chest§r with the plate is found.

Please note that while they're often in a big crater, the meteors might be buried underground; when the compass is spinning wildly, you're right on top of one.

The Eighth Micro Miner.

The main source of §6Chaos Shards§r.

The other mission gives negligible amounts of §6Neutronium§r and some other moderately useful things, but you're better off making Neutronium in the §3Fusion Reactor Mark 3§r and the other items are otherwise craftable.

§6Chaos Shards§r are an endgame component for §bDraconic Evolution§r.

They are the base material for Chaotic Tier materials and come exclusively from Tier Eight Micro Miners. You'll need the Tier Seven Micro Miner for the §6Lair of the Chaos Dragon Data§r.

The Ninth Micro Miner.

Combines §bStellar Creation Data§r into the §dUniverse Creation Data§r, which is a crucial component for the Tier Ten Micro Miner mission.

The alternate mission brings a large quantity of §6Neutronium§r. It might be easier to just make all your Neutronium in the reactor, but it's up to you.
§2Double Plates§r used exclusively for the Tier Eight Micro Miner.

The most advanced substrate available, prepared for bleeding-edge bioengineering technology.

§6Wetware Circuit Boards§r are the basis of §6Wetware§r circuits, the final theme that spans tiers six through nine.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§6Awakened Draconium§r, §6Chaos Shards§r, and §6Stabilized Einsteinium§r can be used in a Draconic Tier fusion crafting setup to create a §6Draconic Reactor Core§r.

This is an important component in the Tier Nine and Tier Ten Micro Miners, as well as some Endgame items.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

This quest, and the ones that follow it, are §cNOT REQUIRED§r for progression.

Only do them if you want to be able to explore the various planets offered by Advanced Rocketry and potentially build bases there, or in space.

A space station offers a cool base location with §ano night§r, but you will have to contend with §clow gravity§r, §cno oxygen§r and §cno mob/critter spawning§r

Refer to the various high quality tutorials on AR available on YouTube for specifics.

The §3Warp Core§r is a multiblock structure that you can build on the space station. Use the Holo-Projector for a building guide.

While it's not required for the progression, you can spend some resources to travel to distant planets, either to explore them or just to change the background of your space station. You can really go anywhere, but the §eSun§r offers a black-hole like background that may suit your tastes.

The Input Hatch must be filled with §6Dilithium§r.

§6Dilithium Crystals§r are used to power Warp Cores, and are also a key component in several Micro Miner missions.

They are made by crystallizing §6Dilithium Dust§r with §9Deuterium§r in an §3Autoclave§r.

The Fourth Micro Miner.

All of the Tier Four missions require §68 Quantum Flux§r and a stack of §6Petrotheum Dust§r.

This miner is the first convenient source of §6Osmium§r and §6Iridium§r, via a mission requiring §6Wither Realm Data§r.

A §6Composition Sensor§r instead directs the miner to obtain §6Dense Oilsands Ore§r, equivalent to §232§r stacks of §6End Oilsands Ore§r, and 32 §6Compressed Infinity Dust Blocks§r, equivalent to 2592 §6Infinity Dust§r.

When equipped with a §6Gemstone Sensor§r:
§6* Dense Lapis Ore
* Dense Diamond Ore
* Dense Coal Ore
* Dense Emerald Ore
* Dense Redstone Ore§r

The Fifth Micro Miner.

The only source of §6Naquadah §2Ore§r. Along with it, §2Sheldonite Ore§r (for §6PGS§r) and §2Kaemanite Ore§r (for §6Trinium§r), via a mission with §6Stabilized Plutonium§r.

When provided with §6Stabilized Uranium§r, brings:
§2* Uraninite Ore
§6* Palladium Ore
§2* Realgar Ore
§6* Bastnasite Ore
* Sphalerite Ore
* Monazite Ore
§2* Enderpearl Blocks
* Osmiridium 80/20 Ore
§6* Boron Dust
* Molybdenite Ore
* Beryllium Ore§r

§6Iridium§r is an advanced material used for Micro Miners, and for alloying with §6Osmium§r into §6Osmiridium§r.

You can also get tons of these from §6Platinum Group Sludge§r.

§2Osmiridium 80/20 Ore and Iridosmine 80/20 Ore§r is available renewably from the Tier Four and Tier Six micro miners, as well as semi-renewably from the Tier Five micro miner.

The Sixth Micro Miner.

The first decent source of §6Dragon Eggs§r and §6Stabilized Einsteinium§r.

Is also useful for:
§2* Uraninite Ore
* Iridosmine 80/20 Ore
* Osmiridium 80/20 Ore§r

An alloy of equal parts §6Tungsten§r and §6Carbon Dust§r.

§6Tungsten Carbide§r is a very dense, sturdy, and heat-resistant material useful for a variety of applications.

The Seventh Micro Miner.

The source of §6Dragon Hearts§r and the valuable §6Lair of The Chaos Guardian Data§r.

As a bonus, brings §6Dragon Eggs, Dragon's Breath, Ender Dragon Scales§r, §2Ruthenium Blocks§r and a plenty of different precious metals and gems.
§2Double Plates§r used exclusively for the Tier Seven Micro Miner.

§6Awakened Draconium§r is a powerful material used for crafting high-grade components, items, and machines from §bDraconic Evolution§r.

Five §6Draconium Blocks§r can be processed in a Wyvern Tier fusion crafting setup to create an equal output of five §6Awakened Draconium Blocks§r. At §e24 Billion RF per craft§r, you better have a handle on your power infrastructure.

Your first MV hull is as good of a place as any to consider yourself graduated from LV.

You might notice that these hulls can be made more cheaply in an §3Assembling Machine§r, but you don't have that weird fluid. Don't worry, you'll be able to make that soon.

§2Overclocking mechanics have changed in CEu. All overclocks now multiply the speed by 2.0x (instead of the 2.0/2.8 split in CE). This means that to save energy, you should build more low-tier machines over overclocking a high-tier machine, especially for passive processes.
Additionally, ULV recipes will not overclock to LV. A ≤8 EU/t recipe won't overclock at all in an LV machine, will only overclock once in an MV machine, etc.§r

§3Electrolyzers§r use electricity to separate items into their more basic components.

For example, you can break down Water into §9Hydrogen Gas§r and §9Oxygen Gas§r, or break down §6Clay Dust§r into §6Sodium Dust§r, §6Silicon Dust§r, §6Lithium Dust§r, and §6Aluminium Dust§r.

Having unlocked §6Signalum§r and §6Lumium§r, at long last you can now make §aSignalum Upgrade Kits§r!

Provides more augment slots to machines and dynamos.

Dynamos operate at §a500% of base power and fuel burn rate§r.

Portable Tanks hold §a800 buckets§r.

Machines operate at §a400% of base speed§r.
An advanced ingredient used for the §aUltimate Extended Crafting Table§r and other late-game recipes.

§6Indium§r is a rare material requiring specialized bulk ore processing to acquire. It is useful for making §6Indium Gallium Phosphide§r (InGaP).

You will need to purify (with a §3Washer§r or §3Chemical Bath§r) §6Galena§r and §6Sphalerite§r to get §6Crushed Purified§r dusts. These need to be placed together in a §3Chemical Reactor§r along with §9Sulfuric Acid§r, which will result in §9Indium Concentrate§r.

This in turn needs to be reacted with §6Aluminium§r in another Chemical Reactor, to create §2Indium Dust§r, §2Aluminium Sulfite§r and §9Lead-Zinc Solution§r. The latter two can be broken down into various useful materials.

There is an alternative recipe set to §9Programmed Circuit §64§r, which performs the recipe in a larger batch and allows you to §2skip combining small piles into full dusts.

Indium can also be obtained from the Naquadah processing chain in LuV.§r

With your new §6Epoxy Circuit Boards, QBit CPUs§r, and some standard components, you can make the final type of Tier Four Circuit: the §6Quantum Circuit§r.

As the best form of Tier Four circuit, these should be automated and stockpiled. The variant recipe requiring §6Advanced System-on-Chip§r won't be available until ZPM.
betterquesting:10.name:8: The Third And Final Tier Four Circuits

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§6QBit CPUs§r are an advanced Circuit Wafer crucial for §6Quantum Circuits§r.

There are two methods of creating them:

The simpler recipe uses two §6Quantum Eyes§r and two ingots worth of molten §9Gallium Arsenide§r to enhance a §6NanoCPU Wafer§r. This recipe is slow and requires substantially more §9Radon§r per craft.

The other route instead uses §6Indium Gallium Phosphide§r and a tiny amount of Radon. This skips the slow-crafting Quantum Eyes, using far less Radon in the process, but requires the infrastructure in place for obtaining §6Indium§r.

The second route is overall better, and you will need Indium processing to complete the pack so might as well do it.

§2Item Pipes are back in GTCEu! They will transport items instantly through them.§r

This quest accepts a item pipe of any material, any size, whether restrictive or normal.

For now, the best material to make these pipes out of is probably §6Tin§r.

Their advantage over §5EnderIO §3Item Conduits§r is their far higher §6throughput§r. An unupgraded EIO Item Conduit transports §d8 items per second§r, and up to §d128§r when upgraded. In comparison, small low-tier Item Pipes can transfer §d64 items per second§r, and those made from later materials can transfer §dmultiple stacks per second§r.

They don't auto-extract by themselves, so you have to use §3Conveyor covers§r etc. with them.

The priority mechanics are more complicated, so skip ahead if you are not interested:
A Destination will have a Routing Value calculated, which is the sum of all Routing Values of the individual Pipes to that Destination. Whichever Destination has the lowest Routing Value will be the one selected for Insertion.
Restrictive Pipes typically have the lowest Priority for insertion due to their higher Routing Value.

§9Radon§r will be needed in large quantities.

For now, you'll need to obtain it from Tier Two Micro Miner missions, in the form of §6Radium Salt§r. Electrolyze it for Radon and §6Rock Salt§r. §2You can also get it from distilling liquid Ender Air.§r

Later it will be possible to make Radon using a §bGregTech §3Fusion Reactor§r.
Nothing new here, just use more standard circuit stuff and you can upgrade several §6Quantum Circuits§r into a §6Quantum Processor§r.
Nothing special about this tier either.

§oNote: this quest accepts LV, MV and HV Macerators.

§3Macerators§r are useful for grinding things down, replacing the §aMortars§r you've needed until now. This is an important machine you will be using for many things in the future.

You don't really need a LV one, as you can use the superior §3Steam Grinder§r. LV or MV ones could be used for automation. However, HV ones provide chanced output, extremely important for §eOre Processing§r and other processes.

One useful application for a Macerator in the near future is grinding down §6Clay§r or §6Terracotta§r into §6Clay Dust§r.

Besides not having limited durability, a key advantage of Macerators over Mortars is the chance to get additional materials when grinding things down. These are called §ebyproducts§r, and HV or better Macerators have three slots instead of one so byproducts can appear.

When reading Macerator recipes in §bJEI§r, you can tell which outputs are byproducts by seeing if §ethe tooltip tells you it has a chance to appear§r: guaranteed outputs do not list a chance. §2The chance increases by a certain amount for each tier of machine you have above the tier of recipe. This chance is also listed in the tooltip.

Macerators can now also recycle your old Machines for some extra materials.§r

Finally, a Macerator will only start processing if there is room for all possible outputs. Make sure you empty them so they can keep working.

The §6Reactor Stabilizer§r is a component needed for the Tier Nine and Tier Ten Micro Miners, as well as a component in a few Endgame recipes.

They are made in a Chaotic Tier fusion crafting setup, requiring a whopping §e56 Billion total RF each§r. You're gonna need some serious power generation and crafting infrastructure to make everything for these.

The first tier of §6capacitors§r. These (or stronger versions) are required to make §bEnderIO§r machines run. They're also used as components in a variety of recipes.

Higher tier capacitors will significantly increase the speed at which these machines operate, among other machine-specific properties.

Mixes two dusts to make a third.

For now, you'll be using it to make §2Energetic Alloy Dust§r and §6Glowstone Dust§r.

Glowstone Dust is made from §6Tricalcium Phosphate Dust§r and §6Gold Dust§r, or you could eventually gather it from the Nether.
§6Dragon Hearts§r are needed for both §6Awakened Draconium§r and §6The Ultimate Material§r.
§6Luminessence§r is used in a number of things, but right now, it will be a component in your §aExtended Crafting Tables§r.

§9Phosphoric Acid§r is a key component of §6Luminessence§r, which will be used extensively for such things as §6Nether Stars§r, §6Lumium Blend§r, and §bExtended Crafting§r components.

It can be made using several equally viable recipes:

§6Phosphorus§r, §9Oxygen§r, and §9Water§r can be chemically reacted to produce §9Phosphoric Acid§r.

Alternatively, you can combine §6Phosphorus Pentoxide§r and Water for a much faster reaction.

Otherwise, you can react §6Apatite Dust§r, §9Sulfuric Acid§r, and Water to get Phosphoric Acid, §9Hydrochloric Acid§r, and a whole bunch of §6Gypsum Dust§r.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

You can combine various items with a §6Blank Data Model§r for a completed §6Data Model§r that you can run inside the §3Simulation Chamber§r.

You will also need §6Pulsating Polymer Clay§r in order to run those simulations. The §3Simulation Chamber§r consumes one §6Pulsating Polymer Clay§r per operation.

"§6Dragon Eggs§r?" You might ask. Yep.

The final circuit theme, Wetware, will require a lot of them.

Tier Six Micro Miners can get some eggs (enough for this quest, as it happens), but Tier Seven miners are a better long-term solution for building up your supply, as they also give §6Dragon Hearts§r.

Later, you'll also get substantial quantities from Tier Eight Micro Miners, while you are accumulating §6Chaos Shards§r.

Man, that's a LOT of quests linked to this one.

§dOmnium§r, as the name suggests, is an incredible material composed of all elements and alloys you've encountered so far.

Fun fact: you'll need to make 487 motes. You've got all this automated, right?
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§eNote: text like <{link}>https://github.com/Nomi-CEu/<|>this<{link}> are clickable links!§r

This is your entry point into the world of §bApplied Energistics 2§r.

If you are new to this mod, you probably want to check out some guides, because using this mod effectively will be critical.

We recommend <{link}>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u0ouTWgdcXk<|>Pansmith's AE2 Guide<{link}>, and if you're looking for something in a playthough context, check out <{link}>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ReMrvfSWIhI&list=PLitR_6VqTWIBNll_vxvfRkCUeUA1-QJMP<|>Threefold's Nomi Playthrough<{link}>. However, note that the playthrough is for §eNomi CE§r. Whilst some AE2 mechanics are the same, there have been §emany new features§r and therefore §amany new techniques§r since then, so always refer back to this quest book.

Of course, other guides are also helpful. Just remember: §echannels are disabled in this pack§r, and there are many changes to recipes, as well as AE2 addon mods such as §bAE2 Stuff§r and §bNAE2§r.

Fluix is initially made via in-world crafting, by dropping §6Redstone§r, §6Nether Quartz§r, and a §6Charged Certus Quartz Crystal§r in the same block of §9Water§r. You'll see some sparks then the items will merge into a §6Fluix Crystal§r. Be sure to turn off any nearby item magnets/collectors or they might interrupt this crafting process.

The §3Energy Acceptor§r converts RF power into AE power that Applied Energistics uses, in a 2 RF to 1 AE ratio. This power will be transmitted through adjacent full-block ME Network devices, as well as along all connected §6ME Cables§r, §6ME Conduits§r, and §6Quartz Fiber§r.

Quartz Fiber are §emicroparts§r you can put between an ME Cable and any ME Network block or another ME Cable. This will allow transmission of AE power but not data, which is useful for having data-isolated ME Networks all sharing the same power source.

With your §2Rhodium Plated Lumium-Palladium§r-based machine hulls, Assembling Machine built, and §6Quantum Processor Mainframes§r squared away, you can finally get on the path to making a Ludicrous Voltage §3Circuit Assembling Machine§r.

This tier of Assembling Machine unlocks §6Crystal Circuits§r, as well as handling crafting recipes up to 32768 EU/t. It can also optionally overclock recipes that consume up to 8192 EU/t for improved speed at the cost of relatively more power.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

Starting at §5EV§r tier, §aQuadruple§r and §aNonuple Input Hatches§r and §aOutput Hatches§r are available. They essentially act as 4 or 9 different Input or Output Hatches for multiblocks in a single block. This should come in handy for §3Large Chemical Reactor§r work.

Higher tier hatches increase the capacity, like normal hatches.

Note that certain multiblocks, such as the §3Distillation Tower§r, do not accept these hatches. Check §eJEI§r if you run into issues.

The §3Assembly Line§r is a large multiblock structure that crafts complex materials, similar to an §3Assembling Machine§r. These will be crucial going forward for making a variety of components and machinery.

Make sure your power generation and circuit production are up to the challenge. §2None of the Assembly Line recipes require programmed circuits anymore.§r It is §anot required§r to insert items or fluids in the correct order.

Notice that all numbers of required items are §emultiples of 10.§r This is to make an Assembly Line that's 10 units long, allowing for 9 inputs and one output. This is a large enough Assembly Line to make §6LuV components§r, but you'll need to expand to more inputs for later projects.

The structure of the Assembly Line is a little stricter than other multiblocks:

- The §aInput Buses§r can only be placed along the bottom, must all be §8ULV§r tier, and must face downwards. The §aOutput Bus§r must be placed at the very end of the row of Input Buses, and can be any tier.

- §aFluid Hatches§r and the §2Maintenance Hatch§r can only replace the §6Steel Casings§r along the bottom.

- §aEnergy Hatches§r can only be placed within the top row of §6Steel Casings§r.

- The §2Data Access Hatch§r must replace a §6Grate Casing§r on the same side as the Assembly Line controller block. Later, you can replace this with an §2Optical Data Reception Hatch§r. Refer to adjacent quests for how the Assembly Line data system works.

If your recipe is not running, ensure you have the corresponding §edata§r for the recipe in a §2Data Access Hatch§r or connected §3Data Bank§r.

Time to get fusing!

The §3Fusion Reactor§r is a multiblock that uses enormous amounts of energy to fuse fluids into new elements. This one is less flexible than the previous GregTech multiblocks, as you can only put hatches where the preview shows. §6Sneak-right click§r the controller to enable the in-world preview.

The §bJEI§r preview shows §eall valid hatch locations§r, but you don't actually need that many fluid hatches. You can replace any of the hatch positions in the structure with §2Fusion Machine Casings§r as long as you have at least §atwo Fluid Input Hatches§r and §aone Fluid Output Hatch§r. It's possible to use input/output hatches in every valid location, if you prefer.

Because of this, the quest only asks for §248 Fusion Machine Casings§r. If you want to use the minimum number of fluid hatches, you'll need to craft an additional §229 Fusion Machine Casings§r. In addition to the §a48 Fusion Machine Casings§r, you will also need §631 Fusion Glass§r or §631 Fusion Machine Casings§r. §bFusion Glass is cheaper, and looks cooler§r, but its your choice.

Each §aEnergy Hatch§r increases the reactor's power buffer. §2You cannot use 4x or 16x Energy Hatches in Fusion Reactors. §aAll 16 Energy Hatches§r are required to be able to process all Mark 1 recipes and give a power buffer of §e160M EU§r. §2However, not all energy hatches are needed to be connected to power.§r For example, a recipe that requires §dLuV§r power draw would only need §aone or more hatches connected to power§r. §cThey still need to be present on the structure!§r

In addition to the recipe power drain, Fusion Reactors have a §eheat§r mechanic related to the recipe's §e"Eu to Start"§r. This amount of power is drained from the reactor's buffer before starting the recipe to heat up the reactor to the necessary temperature, and is independent of the recipe's EU/t cost. As such, this determines the minimum tier of reactor you need for a recipe.

If the reactor stops processing, it will §erapidly lose heat§r, even if you pause it with a soft hammer. On the other hand, if the reactor is already at the required temperature for a recipe, §eno additional power§r is required to heat up the reactor! This is true even if you switch between different recipes. This mechanic incentivizes continuous use of the reactor.

If you switch to a recipe that requires more heat, §eonly the difference§r in heat values is consumed as EU to reach the target heat (up to a maximum heat equal to the reactor's current buffer).

Fusion Reactors §2overclock, but only once per fusion tier, instead of based on energy input.§r They gate the next tier of materials, so you will eventually want to make more than one.

You'll need at least §6Naquadah Coil Blocks§r in your blast furnace to smelt §6Draconium§r, as well as a healthy supply of §2Cetane-Boosted Diesel or Gasoline§r to reach the immense heat it takes to liquefy.

Draconium gets so hot that it requires the potent coolant §9Gelid Cryotheum§r to aid your §3Vacuum Freezer§r in turning it into usable ingots.

There are several ways to make Draconium: dust can be smelted into ingots, but you can also turn §6Ender Dragon Scales§r, which contain Draconium, directly into ingots. It uses a lot of §2combustion fuel§r, but is the most efficient way to craft Draconium.

You've been stockpiling fuel, right?

By baking a §2Raw Crystal Chip§r and §6Emerald Plates§r with §9Helium§r in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r, you can create an §6Engraved Crystal Chip§r.

This is a material needed for §6Crystal Circuits§r.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§6Crystal CPUs§r are the cores of §6Crystal Circuits§r.

You'll need an §2LuV Precision Laser Engraver§r to craft this.
With some now-standard components you can upgrade a few §6Crystal Circuits§r into a §6Crystal Processor§r.

The culmination of so much effort.

§6Chaotic Cores§r are the ultimate tier of §bDraconic Evolution§r core, used for the most powerful and advanced items.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Restonia Crystal§r.

Made from fluid solidification.

§bDraconic Evolution§r features §eFusion Crafting§r, which requires a §6Fusion Crafting Core§r and up to ten injectors of the appropriate tier.

You'll need a setup with eight §6Basic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r to upgrade any additional injectors you make to Wyvern Tier.

Obtaining §6Grains of Infinity§r will require you to mine all the way down to Bedrock level.

Use Flint and Steel to light a fire (or many fires) and then wait for it to go out. There's a 50% chance of Grains Of Infinity to appear for every fire that burns out on its own.

Don't worry, you'll be able to use §aFire Water§r, §aBlazing Pyrotheum§r or §aTier Four Microminers§r to get grains before long.

Mixing §6Titanium§r with §6Mana Dust§r creates §6Mana Infused Metal Dust§r. This can be smelted into ingots in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r equipped with §6Kanthal Coils§r or better.

Mana Infused Metal is the basis of §bThermal Expansion§r device casings, and is used for many advanced §aAugments§r.

ASSEMBLE!

§6Mana Dust§r is an important material. It is needed for a variety of materials related to §bThermal Expansion§r.
This casing is the structure for §bThermal Expansion§r's devices, which are simpler machines.

§6Thermal Device Casings§r are upgradable to a §6Machine Frame§r with some §6Stainless Steel Plates§r.

These frames form the basis of §bThermal Expansion§r's more advanced machinery.
§6Redstone§r, a §6Snowball§r, and §6Blizz Powder§r creates §6Cryotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental frost.
§6Redstone§r, §6Saltpeter§r, and §6Blitz Powder§r creates §6Aerotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental air.
§6Redstone§r, §6Obsidian Dust§r, and §6Basalz Powder§r creates §6Petrotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental earth.
§6Redstone§r, §6Sulfur§r, and §6Blaze Powder§r creates §6Pyrotheum Dust§r, a mixture imbued with potent elemental flame.
Bits of a §6Blaze Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.
Bits of a §6Basalz Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.
Bits of a §6Blitz Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.
Bits of a §6Blizz Rod§r. Using a §3Macerator§r doubles your yield.

If you don't feel like searching for a Thermal Elemental, or can't because you're playing on Peaceful, you will need to make §eone§r batch of §9Elemental Reduction Fluid§r.

This will bootstrap being able to craft a §aThermal Elemental Model§r for DME, and you can get all of the rods from §6Thermal Elemental Pristine Matter§r going forward.

Praise the sun. \[T]/

This machine uses various tiers of §6Phyto-Gro§r and §9Water§r to grow plants.

It can be customized with various §aAugments§r.
§6RTM Alloy§r is the fourth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 4500K so it can process more advanced materials.

§6HSS-G§r is an alloy of §6Tungstensteel§r, §6Chrome§r, §6Molybdenum§r, and §6Vanadium§r.

This alloy is cooked in an §3Electric Blast Furnace§r and cooled in a §3Vacuum Freezer§r.
§6HSS-G§r is the fifth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 5400K so it can process more advanced materials, such as §6Naquadah§r.

Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.
A complex plating material used exclusively for the Tier Nine Micro Miner.

§2The Naphtha route for Epoxy has been removed. You can only make Epoxy using the BPA route.§r

BPA can be produced using petrochemistry distillation products, or via distilling §9Charcoal Byproducts§r from your §3Pyrolyse Oven§r into useful components. Alternatively, you can get §9Phenol§r from §6Coal§r pyrolysis. §9Fermented Biomass§r is also useful to distill as it provides many useful products.

§2Using the Large Chemical Reactor, you can skip two steps in the Epoxy production line.§r

You'll need large quantities of §6Canola§r (for §6Canola Oil§r in a §bCanola Press§r) and §6Sugarcane§r (for §6Ethanol§r).

Of course, other crops can work as well, if you want to mix things up.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Void Crystal§r.

Made from fluid solidification.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Palis Crystal§r.

Made from fluid solidification.

A gear forged from §6Empowered Emeradic Crystal§r.

Made from fluid solidification.

An otherworldly material exclusive to Microverses, §6Naquadah§r is an important material in the late game.

It can be alloyed and enriched to various forms, and is the eventual source of §6Neutronium§r in a §3Mark Three Fusion Reactor§r.

§6Naquadah§r is the sixth coil material available, increasing your EBF's operating temperature to 7200K so it can process more advanced materials.

§2You cannot skip a coil material anymore.§r

With a §3Fusion Reactor§r, you can make Europium!

This element is needed for making things in §bDraconic Evolution§r, as well as the §6Fusion Reactor Computer Mark 2§r, §2Crystal Chip growing§r, and §6Wetware Supercomputers§r.

You make it by fusing molten §9Neodymium§r and §9Hydrogen§r.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

Just ignore the protesters outside your base.

Each craft in an §3LuV Chemical Reactor§r takes five minutes, so it's probably a good idea to have more than one machine running this recipe. At least you get §2128 from a single craft.§r
§6Boron§r is currently obtainable by doing ore processing on §6Lepidolite Ore§r and §6Salt Ore§r (via §6Borax§r), and later on, it can be obtained via the Tier Five micro miner.

§6Basic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r can be upgraded to Wyvern Tier via fusion crafting.

Technically you only need six of these to start making the next tier of injectors, but some recipes will need more than that. Plan on making at least twenty-six of these.

§6Draconic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r are the penultimate tier of injectors for fusion crafting.

You'll need a fusion crafting setup with ten of these for the next tier of injector, and the next tier you'll also need ten injectors, so consider making 20 of these.

The highest tier of fusion crafting injectors. You will need at least ten of these to reach the §dCreative Tank§r.

Each injector requires four ingots of §6Neutronium§r and four §6Chaos Shards§r, as well as two §6Crystal Matrix§r blocks.

Hope you've got those Tier Eight Micro Miners automated.

The final form of Tier Six circuits, and the final circuit theme.

Using your §2Neuro Processing Units§r, you can craft (grow?) these circuits in a ZPM or better §3Circuit Assembling Machine§r.

These are fairly slow to craft and you're going to need considerable quantities, so make sure you have a good parallelized infrastructure for keeping these stocked.
betterquesting:10.name:8: §2The Fourth And Final Tier Six Circuits§r

betterquesting:10.desc:8: §6Wetware Processors§r are made in §2the ZPM+ Circuit Assembler still.§r
betterquesting:10.name:8: §2The Third and Final Tier Seven Circuits§r

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§6Wetware Supercomputers§r are made in an §3Assembly Line§r at ZPM or better power.

You'll need §6Europium§r from the §3Fusion Reactor§r to craft these.
betterquesting:10.name:8: The Second And Final Tier Eight Circuits

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The final circuit!

The only novel ingredient is §6Tritanium Frames§r.

§6Wetware Processor Mainframes§r are unique in that there are no subsequent circuit themes, and thus no other kinds of Tier Nine circuits. Unlike past mainframes, you will need to craft more than just a few of them. They're mostly used in the Endgame though, so you don't have to worry too much yet.

Definitely consider parallelizing your §3Assembly Lines§r if you haven't already. Even just having two or three lines will vastly improve your production speeds and help avoid bottlenecks as you push towards the Endgame.
betterquesting:10.name:8: The First And Only Tier Nine Circuit

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Draconium is a complex material needed in vast quantities.

You'll likely have come by some dust while mining in the End, but you can also create it with §6Dragon's Breath§r and §6Manyullyn§r.

§6Draconic Cores§r are the first crafting step into §bDraconic Evolution§r.

These serve as the basis for crafting many items and can be upgraded into different tiers of cores via §eFusion Crafting§r.

§2You can make HV Batteries like LV and MV ones, but there is a better option.

Energium Crystals can store 6,400,000 EU, at the cost of some crafting complexity. They need an HV Autoclave.§r

With §6Titanium§r smelting automated, you can now build Machine Hulls for Extreme Voltage machines.

EV motors require a better material than §6Steel§r for its magnetism.

§6Neodymium§r is required, which is mainly achieved from §6Rare Earth§r. The main sources of this are §6Redstone§r, and everything inside of §6Bastnasite§r veins.

EV Machine Hulls unlock a handful of nice things, including shortcut recipes for §bAE2 §6Fluix and Pure Crystals§r in the §3Autoclave§r. Check the surrounding quests for other useful features.

An Extreme Voltage tier §bGregTech§r battery.

§2Higher tier GT Batteries have been buffed to be quite strong - this one holds 25 MEU, or 100 MRF. You may want to consider using them over RF storage.§r
An Insane Voltage tier §bGregTech§r battery. §2Equivalent to 40 Vibrant Capacitor Banks!§r
A Ludicrous Voltage tier §bGregTech§r battery.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§3The Empowerer§r is a machine from §bActually Additions§r used to convert its special crystalline materials into empowered variants.

The Empowerer is placed in the center of a flat 7x7 region. The four §aDisplay Stands§r are placed with a two-block gap from the Empowerer, one in each cardinal direction.

Recipes require specific items to be placed on the Display Stands and the main item on the Empowerer itself. The items on the Display Stands are consumed and the central item is Empowered.

RF power needs to be fed into the Display Stands to infuse the center item with power. The Display Stands have a low per-side power transfer rate so it takes a while. Consider putting energy conduits on multiple sides of each display stand to speed it up a bit.


If you've used the Empowerer before you'll know that this thing's a bit of a pain. It's slow, takes up a large space, and it's cumbersome to automate.

Don't worry, you'll get access to the §3Combination Package Crafter§r after you get §6Draconium§r, which is vastly faster, more compact and easier to automate. This lets you do Empowerer recipes directly through §bPackagedAuto§r and §bAE2§r. However, some optional paths like §9Bio-Diesel§r involve early Empowerer use.

§6Wyvern Cores§r are the second tier of cores, used for intermediate crafting recipes.

Each Wyvern Core is made via fusion crafting and the setup needs eight §6Basic Fusion Crafting Injectors§r.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§6Steel §2Double Plates§r can be augmented with §6Tungsten Plates§r and §6Tough Alloy§r to make §6Basic Reactor Plating§r.

That's right-- it's time to get into §bNuclearCraft§r.

Enhancing basic plating with §6YBCO§r and §6Hard Carbon alloy§r results in a better plating material for more advanced §bNuclearCraft§r blocks.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

The full complexity of §bNuclearCraft§r is far too much for the scope of this quest guide, so §eyou're encouraged to watch a tutorial or read a guide online§r. However, the surrounding quests will give you a general overview, and lead towards resources to plan your reactors.

§aIn Nomi-CEu, Fission Reactors will not meltdown when overheated!§r However, power production and fuel consumption will §cstop§r until the heat is reduced, so having a reactor overheat will most likely not be efficient.

There are six main parts to a reactor:

* §eThe Controller§r: Controls whether the reactor is turned on, and allows manual accessing of reactor fuels and products. By default, a reactor is off, and is only turned on when a §credstone signal§r is provided. §cRequired for a reactor to form.§r

* §eFission Casings§r: These come in opaque and transparent variants, and must form a solid box around the reactor contents. §aThe edges may be excluded. §cRequired for a reactor to form.§r

* §eFission Buffers§r: Allow extra access points for automation to access reactor fuels, products and power storage. Also allows entry points for coolant. Replaces Fission Casing locations. §eOptional.§r

* §eReactor Cells§r: These are the main component for reactors, and is where the reaction 'takes place'. More reactor cells leads to higher fuel consumption, more heat generated, and more power generated. §cRequired for a reactor to operate.§r

* §eModerator Blocks§r: These increase power generation and fuel efficiency, at the expense of increasing heat generated. §eOptional.§r

* §ePassive Coolers§r: These are the main way to cool a fission reactor, and they have special placement rules, as seen by their tooltip. Fission reactors must be cooled, preferably at a similar amount as the heat produced. §cRequired for a reactor to operate.§r

* §eActive Coolers§r: These are the only blocks inside a fission reactor that actively consumes resources, which can be piped in by buffers, or by other methods such as §3Phantom Liquifaces§r. They consume §a10 mb/s§r of coolant, in exchange for a lot more cooling than passive coolers provide. Note that they abide by the same placement rules as their passive counterparts. §cIf coolant runs out, active coolers produce no cooling! §eOptional.§r

Check out the surrounding quests for how to proceed with fission: a process that will net you §6valuable resources§r, and be a §6powerful power generator§r.

You don't need it just yet, but you can make it now.

This is a critical material for the Endgame.
§3Fluid Solidifiers§r are useful for lots of things too, of course. Look through the various molds to see what you can make with one. §aGears§r and §aRotors§r may be the most useful.

The §aHang Glider§r is a great way to cross long distances, if you're so inclined.

If you don't want to go exploring for Cows, just buy a pair of "§6Spawn Cow§r" eggs and breed them. Seriously, spend your §dcoins§r!

A gear forged from §6Empowered Enori Crystal§r.

Made from fluid solidification.
A catalyst forged from §dOmnium§r, §6Empowered Gears§r, various enhanced §6Nether Stars§r, and a core made of §6The Ultimate Material§r.

Are you ready to go infinite?

Reinforcing §6Heart of a Universe§r with §6Chaotic Cores§r, many §6Piles of Neutrons§r, and a bunch of §6Eternal Catalysts§r produces an §cInfinity Catalyst§r.

This material is the core of most creative-tier crafting recipes.

This ingot is the most advanced basic material.

With creative fluids and all the automation you hopefully set up for your first §cInfinity Catalyst§r, these ingots should be easy.

Well, not easy. But... Reasonable.

From here, you are going to be crafting a multitude of Creative-Tier items from various mods. In addition to being useful for their regular functionality, they are needed for the final goal: the §dCreative Chest§r.

§bJEI§r is your friend: beyond noting a few more items, I will not be holding your hand anymore. I've taught you everything you need to know to beat the pack.

You can do it!
A helmet to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
A chestplate to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
Leggings to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
Boots to surpass the ultimate, forged with the hearts of stars and the raw fury of the universe.
An ultimate helmet, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.
An ultimate chestplate, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.
An ultimate pair of boots, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.
An ultimate pair of leggings, forged from all manner of materials across dimensions and microverses.

You win.

Congratulations.

I hope you enjoyed playing §5Nomifactory§r.

§oNow this is not the end. It is not even the beginning of the end. But it is, perhaps, the end of the beginning.§r

The §dCreative Tank§r is a major milestone. Great work!

This tank is your first proper creative item, which can be set to a fluid and then provides an infinite quantity of that fluid. §2Use the Creative Tank Provider to supply you with Creative Tanks.

The GT Creative Tank has been enhanced. You can turn it on and off, configure exactly how much fluid you want it to push and how often, and change which direction the fluid is pushed out. You can even configure the fluid you want directly from JEI!§r

From there you can set up tanks with infinite quantities of every fluid you can think of. §3Fluid Solidifiers §2or the much more powerful Large Solidification Arrays§r can be used to make infinite of every element you can melt and solidify.

This is quite a game-changer as far as infrastructure goes. You'll find that many machines won't need to be used for their original purpose anymore. Some major base redesign is in order. Have you considered moving to space?

All that said, §ethe pack will still be challenging to complete§r. Infinite resources and power is nice, but it's not everything. There are plenty of materials you can't melt, and creative items will push your factory automation engineering skills to their limits.

Onward to the final challenge: the §dCreative Chest§r!

You may wish to §aautomatically sprint§r, instead of having to press §eControl + W§r or §eW twice§r. To achieve this, change the §bSprint§r keybind to §eW§r. (or the same keybind as Move Forward)

A §aGrappling Hook§r is also very useful in an urban environment, allowing you to climb buildings with ease!

There are lots of ways to upgrade and improve your Grappling Hook, so play around with it.

Open your inventory and look for the Baubles button, click it to reveal the additional bauble slots and put the Hook there.

The default key is §6C§r, however you can change this as you wish. Just be careful of §cKeybind Conflicts§r!
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

No hoops to jump through here. Smelt §6Wood Logs§r to get §6Charcoal§r. It will serve you well as a fuel source until you locate a vein of §6Coal§r.

You might want to craft Charcoal into §6Tiny Charcoal§r pieces to save some fuel. One tiny piece is enough to smelt exactly one item. Just put charcoal into the crafting grid to make some!

You can also make §6Tiny Coal§r in the same way.

A §aSoft Mallet§r can be used to temporarily stop a machine from functioning. This is useful when you have two machines running and both are unable to keep going because of a lack of power... let one finish then turn the other one back on with a second hit from the mallet.

Although you can make it out of §6Wood§r, it is probably better to make it out of §6Rubber§r.

This quest accepts a §aSoft Mallet§r made from any material.

A component used for more advanced items related to §bExtended Crafting§r.
Again, combining a few Components will make a Catalyst.
This table allows you to craft 7x7 Extended Crafting Table recipes.
Combine several components into a catalyst.

Used for Ultimate tier §bExtended Crafting§r.

Don't worry if you can't make these for a while. You'll probably get to them around IV power.
This is the largest Extended Crafting Table, capable of handling 9x9 recipes.

Infuses things with Redstone Flux.

This is useful for charging RF-powered devices, but it also can also charge §6Rich Phyto-Gro§r into §6Fluxed Phyto-Gro§r, and charge §6Certus Quartz Crystals§r into §6Charged Certus Quartz Crystals§r.

ASSEMBLE... TOO!

Yeah you get to craft §6Nether Stars§r. Cool huh?

Over the course of the pack, Nether Stars are going to be needed in quantities that far exceed a reasonable player's ability to farm Withers. §eCraft them, don't bother trying to farm them.§r

Congratulations! You've reached the end of the circuit progression.

The only UHV circuit is the §6Wetware Mainframe§r, which is used for crafting high-tier micro miners among some endgame stuff.

You might be wondering what chunkloading options there are in the pack.

Open your inventory and look at the top-left corner of the screen. Click the map-looking icon called §eClaimed Chunks§r.

§6Click a chunk§r to claim it as yours. This will prevent unwanted creeper explosions and other players from interacting with your base.

§6Shift-left click a claimed chunk§r to load it. This will ensure that the chunk is loaded at all times, even when you're not there. Alternatively, there are §achunk-loading wards§r from §bExtra Utilities§r.

§eIf you're playing on a server with custom settings, ask the server owner what methods are available§r.

To invite players to your §bFTB Utils§r party, look for a corresponding button in the same corner. Parties share claimed chunks with each other. You can configure permissions for your party's claimed chunks in the party settings menu.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Claim Your Chunks and Invite Teammates!

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Basic §aFlux Capacitors§r hold a whopping lot of energy - §a10 million RF§r - and are useful for keeping your §aRF-powered§r equipment and tools charged.

To charge it, you have several options:

- Placing it in a §bGregTech §3Machine§r's charger slot, which charges it at 1 amp (or at §7LV§r, 32 EU/t or 128 RF/t)

- Placing it in a §bGregTech §3Battery Buffer§r, which charges it at 2 amps (or at §7LV§r, 64 EU/t or 256 RF/t)

- Placing it in a §bGregTech §3Turbo Charger§r, which charges it at 4 amps (or at §7LV§r, 128 EU/t or 512 RF/t)

Then, hold it and §ashift-right click§r, and it should charge your items with §aRF§r.

§cRF batteries such as Flux Capacitors cannot be drained by Battery Buffers!§r

The Flux Capacitor is a §bBauble§r, so open your inventory and look for the Baubles button, click it to reveal the additional bauble slots menu and put it into any slot you wish.

Finally, you can charge up all those depleted §6Dark Boots§r and §6The Ender§r swords you've looted.

Very fluxy.

A reagent used in the majority of §6Micro Miner§r missions.

There are several ways to produce §6Quantum Flux§r. All are viable, so figure out which one works best for you.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

A single-block solution to all your power needs.

This baby pushes out 2.14 GRF/t per side.

The §3Multi Smelter§r is an absolute smelting unit, and is most likely the best furnace added by a mod.

It's a 3x3x3 multiblock machine capable of §esmelting huge amounts of items per second§r. By upgrading its coils and power tier, it can become capable of smelting up to literal thousands of items per second.

Shift and hover over different coil blocks: they tell you the number of items a Multi Smelter can smelt per operation: §e32 items per level§r. The most basic Multi Smelter essentially does 32 items in the same time as a furnace does one. With a set of §6RTM Alloy§r coil blocks, that jumps to §e128 items per operation§r.

This quest doesn't ask for coils, hatches or buses: feel free to choose whatever combination you want. You'll need §a8 coil blocks§r, §a1 input bus§r, §a1 output bus§r, and §21 maintenance hatch§r, §21 muffler hatch§r, and at least §a1 energy hatch§r, all of any tier.

§3Large Plasma Turbines§r are a powerful late game method of generating power. One Large Plasma Turbine produces §2a base of 16384 EU/t when using an IV Rotor Holder§r.

Generally, the best plasma fuels to use will be §eHelium Plasma§r with a §3Fusion Reactor Mk1§r, §eTin Plasma§r when you upgrade to §3Mk2§r, and §eAmericium Plasma§r when you upgrade to §3Mk3§r. However, the other plasmas are still competitive, and your setup might lend itself better to a different plasma.

The §2Multiblock Builder§r is a convenient new tool you have access to now.

Right-click multiblock controllers to check what block is missing from their structure, or anything else that is making the structure not form.

Shift-right-click multiblock controllers to automatically build multiblocks using the items from your inventory.

This tool is functionally equivalent to the §dMultiblock Helper§r tool in your §6Terminal§r.

§3Anvils§r can be used to repair almost all §bGregTech tools§r!

You might want to get yourself an anvil instead of breaking and crafting new tools every time. Anvils spawn abundantly in §bLost Cities§r buildings, so go and snatch one!

Please note that in §5Nomifactory CEu§r, XP scales linearly.

This means that every XP level §arequires the same amount of XP §e(25 XP)§r, and that higher XP levels §ado not require more XP§r.

Put a damaged tool inside and put some material it's made of. For example, you'll need to put §6Wrought Iron Ingots§r to repair tools made of §6Wrought Iron§r. The only tools unable to be repaired are the mortar and the plunger.

Also, you can now repair your free §6Mining Hammers§r with some §6Diamonds§r!

§bGregTech§r adds a very versatile way of augmenting machines with §aMachine Covers§r. Covers are "upgrades" that you can put on any GregTech machine, chest, or drum to expand its functionality. These are separate on each side of the machine, meaning you can have up to six different covers! To work with covers, you'll need to make yourself a §aScrewdriver§r to configure covers, and a §aCrowbar§r to remove covers without having to break the machine. This quest accepts a §aScrewdriver§r and §aCrowbar§r made from any material.

§eMost covers also have a ULV version, offering a cheaper alternative to LV covers in early game, though they operate slightly slower.§r

Here's a list of some covers there are in the game, and what they do:

- §lConveyor§r: transfers items continuously to or from an adjacent inventory.

- §lPump§r: is much like a §aConveyor§r, but for fluids.

- §lRobotic Arm§r: is much like §aConveyor§r, but has two additional modes:
* §eKeep Exact§r: moves items to keep a stock of at most the specified number of items
* §eSupply Exact§r: transfers precisely the specified number of items per operation.
This cover is very useful for crafting automation.

- §lFluid Regulator§r: is like a §aRobotic Arm§r, but works with fluids instead of items.

- §lShutter§r: prevents automation from interacting with a specific side of a machine.

- §lDetector§r: Available in §aItem§r, §aFluid§r, §aEnergy§r, and §aActivity§r flavours. Emits a Redstone signal depending on the status of whatever it's detecting.

- §lAdvanced Detectors§r: Available as §aItem§r, §aFluid§r, §aEnergy§r, or §aActivity§r, these covers can emit redstone in more ways than their normal counterparts. Specifically, the §aItem§r, §aFluid§r, and §aEnergy§r advanced detectors can emit a latched redstone signal based on the amount of item/fluid between a set min and max, or they can emit redstone signals proportional to the amount of item/fluids between a set min and max. The §aAdvanced Activity Detector§r emits redstone proportional to a machines progress on a recipe

- §lDigital Interface§r: A graphical display for the machine's current status. Can display things like contained fluids, energy levels, etc.

Covers that move items or fluids can have a §aFilter§r placed inside them. These modify the functionality of covers in ways explained in their own quests.

All GregTech machines have one dedicated output side, which can be set by right-clicking a side with a §aGregTech Wrench§r. This is used for ejecting items into an adjacent inventory.

To enable auto-output, open the machine GUI and click one of the buttons in the bottom-left corner: §6orange§r is items and §9blue§r is fluids.

If you want to also be able to insert items into the output side, you'll have to right-click the output side with a §aGregTech Screwdriver§r.

This can be done by directly right clicking on the output side with a screwdriver, or §6shift right-clicking§r with a screwdriver from the machine grid.

These features can be used to chain machines together to make processing pipelines and facilitate crafting automation with §bApplied Energistics 2§r.

You can easily automate most §bGregTech§r machines with §aME Interfaces§r and processing §aPatterns§r early on by using the machines' auto-output feature.

Use a §aGregTech Wrench§r to relocate the output side of a machine where you want it to be, right-click it with a §aGregTech Screwdriver§r to permit input on the output face, then put an ME Interface on that side of the machine.

You can also permit input from the output side by shift-right-clicking with a screwdriver on the output side via the machine grid.

Right-click the machine and enable item auto-output (§6orange box§r in the bottom-left corner of the GUI).

Now, stuff the ME Interface with processing patterns. The next time you order an item, the ME Interface will push ingredients into the machine, and the machine will push outputs back into the Interface once they're ready, completing the craft. No need to use conduits or import buses!

Furthermore, you can use Blocking Mode, which ensures that no items are in the inventory before placing the items in, which is a handy way to prevent conflicts. Even better, blocking mode now ignores Programmable Circuits and Molds! Please note that non-consumable items should stay in the machine, and not be included in the pattern made. Yes, this means you should make a separate machine for each non-consumable, as well as fluids, at least until you get §6Programmed Circuit Cards§r, §6PAs§r and/or §6Large Machines§r.

This modpack has §aCrafting Calculators§r. It has a steep learning curve, but once you manage to learn how to use it, it's going to be your trusty companion in calculating recipe costs.

Craft yourself one and hit the book button in the top-left corner for a quick overview of how it works.

§2The GTCEu Terminal also has an in-built equivalent to the Crafting Calculator, which you may use instead if you prefer.§r

Now that you have §6Osmium§r and §6Iridium§r from the §6Tier Four Micro Miner§r or §6Platinum Group Processing§r, you can begin automating §bExtended Crafting§r recipes. While it is possible to use §6Automation Interfaces§r for this task, you have access to something §ovastly§r better: §bPackagedExCrafting§r.

To begin, you'll need to craft one of each extended §3Package Crafter§r listed on the right. Put an §3Unpackager§r on top of each one, and then a §3Packager §eanywhere§r you want. These are all AE2 devices, so you'll need to connect them to an ME Network.

Next, right-click the §3Package Recipe Encoder§r, and you should see a button saying "Processing": this button cycles through recipe types, including the various Extended Crafting tables. You'll have to choose the appropriate table for the recipe you want to encode.

§6Holders§r must be encoded in pairs: one for the Packager, and one for the Unpackager. Select the appropriate table for the recipe, look up the recipe you want to encode, and press §6[+]§r in §bJEI§r to fill it in. Put two Holders in the top-left slot and press Save to encode the recipe to both of them. Finally, put each Holder into the respective machines.

If you've done everything correctly, you should see the item appear as craftable in a Terminal.

While it might seem that the crafting process is slow, §ePackagedAuto is excellent at parallelizing§r. You can surround an Unpackager with Crafters and it will use all of them. It's also possible to add more Unpackagers with Crafters to keep up with the Packager, as long as the Holders are all the same.

The §3Medium Microverse Projector§r is a more powerful projector required for sending §6Tier Four§r through §6Tier Six Micro Miners§r into microverses.

Initial missions can operate on §eIV power§r, while §eLuV power§r is required for later missions. As with the prior projector, this structure supports overclocking and the position of buses and hatches can be swapped with any §6Microverse Projector Casing§r.

§6Sneak-right click§r the controller to enable the in-world preview.

§bPackagedAuto§r is an addon for §bApplied Energistics 2§r. Its main purpose in §5Nomifactory§r is to allow you to eventually automate §bExtended Crafting§r recipes, but you may come up with other fun uses for it as well.

§bApplied Energistics 2§r stores recipes in §aPatterns§r, but so far they have been limited to at most 9 stacks of items as input (a standard 3x3 crafting grid). PackagedAuto stores recipes in §aPackage Recipe Holders§r, which don't have this limitation. Additionally, each Holder can store up to §e20 different recipes§r. Holders must be encoded in the §3Package Recipe Encoder§r.

In the vast majority of situations you'll need two identically-encoded Holders, as the following machines work together.

The §3Packager§r is a machine that compresses ingredients for a specific recipe into a set of §6Recipe Packages§r. Each package in a set can hold up to 9 stacks of ingredient items. A simple recipe might consist of one package, but a complex recipe can have up to 9 packages in its set (for 81 total item stacks). Packagers can be placed §eanywhere§r on the ME network, as they output produced packages §eback into the ME System§r.

The §3Unpackager§r is a machine that extracts ingredient items from complete sets of Recipe Packages made in a Packager, ejecting the items into an adjacent inventory. It will only extract the items if §eall packages in a set are present§r.

When both a Packager and Unpackager are connected to an ME Network and have the same recipe, the resulting item will appear as craftable in your §aTerminal§r.

§3Packager Extensions§r will act like a clone of an adjacent Packager - including access to patterns in its Package Recipe Holder - allowing you to craft recipe packages faster. Simply place the Packager Extensions around the Packager. Up to 26 extensions in a 3x3x3 cube around the Packager are supported.

Unlike §aRF power§r, which is safe to transport in any §6conduit§r, §aEU power §erequires caution§r. The key is to always §amatch or exceed§r the §eVoltage§r and §eAmperage§r of your power source with your §6cables§r and machines.

§cNEVER§r hook up your Energy Converter to a cable that has fewer §eAmps§r than your Energy Converter or Battery Buffer generates. For example, you must use §64x cable§r for a 4A Converter, and §616x cable§r for a filled 16-slot Battery Buffer. Cables with insufficient amperage rating will §cburn and be destroyed§r.

§2If you are coming from CE - Both the multiple-amp-source and multiple-face-input bugs from CE have been fixed, the energy network now works as intended.§r

Similarly, your cable must match or exceed the §eVoltage§r of your machines, or they will §cburn and be destroyed§r.

§cNEVER§r connect a machine to excessive §eVoltage§r or it will §cvaporize§r. Touching a §6non-superconductor wire§r with connected §aEU power§r will §cinjure or kill you§r, so for your safety, §euse §6cables or superconductors §einstead§r!

§eNote: superconductors, or wires with 0 loss, have no cable variant. Touching superconductor wires will NOT damage you!§r
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

The §3Large Microverse Projector§r is a more powerful projector required for sending §6Tier Seven§r through §6Tier Ten Micro Miners§r into microverses.

Tier Seven missions will operate on §eLuV power§r, but higher energy tiers will be required for later missions. As with the prior projector, this structure supports overclocking and the position of buses and hatches can be swapped with any §6Microverse Projector Casing§r.

§6Sneak-right click§r the controller to enable the in-world preview.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

§2The functions of the Extractor and Fluid Extractor have been combined into a single machine!

§3Extractors§r are useful for melting things into liquids. For example, you can melt down ingots into molten metals, or §6Rubber Sheets§r into liquid §9Rubber§r.

When you have access to §6Steel§r, you can make molds and use §3Fluid Solidifiers§r to form various components more efficiently from fluids, like §6Gears§r.
Unused Gap Quest. Prevents Overriding Of IDs.

Now that you have a §aFlux Capacitor§r to keep things charged, you might consider making yourself a §aFluxomagnet§r.

This relatively inexpensive bauble will suck nearby items into your inventory.
Fish Oil, surprisingly, comes from fish.

A much more efficient version of the §3Empowerer§r.

This is a digital upgrade to the §3Crafting Core§r, allowing you to craft Empowerer recipes directly through §bPackagedAuto§r.

The §aMarked Pedestals§r can be placed freely within three blocks distance of the Crafting block, as long as they are on the same Y-level.

As usual with PackagedAuto crafters, you need to encode the recipe in the correct mode and place a copy in two places: a §3Packager§r somewhere on your network, and an §3Unpackager§r adjacent to the §3Combination Package Crafter§r.

These recipes require large amounts of RF and it §ewill not use power from your §aME Network§r, so you must also connect the package crafter directly to energy conduits.
